    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 is a purist\u2019s specification, featuring the high-revving M96 3.4L flat-six mated to a crisp 6-speed longitudinal manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a multi-link rear suspension setup and MacPherson struts up front, providing that signature telepathic steering feedback. Recent preventative maintenance includes an upgraded IMS bearing and a fresh rear main seal, ensuring the integrity of the intermediate shaft. The naturally aspirated power delivery is linear, pulling hard to the 7,200 RPM redline, while the factory-spec limited-slip differential maximizes traction through the apex. This is a well-sorted driver\u2019s example with a clean underside and a robust service history, ready for the canyons.",
      "price": 34500.0,
